oard/client/route.ts`, to ensure they adhere to enterprise-level style and TypeScript best practices. I want to guarantee they are perfectly clean, correct, and elegant before considering any UI adjustments. The guardrails emphasize avoiding UI changes unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n**Analyzing Auth Caller**\n\nI'm now focusing on the authorization process within `app/api/v1/dashboard/client/route.ts`. I'm closely examining the `getAuthCaller` function, scrutinizing the token verification and user retrieval from the mock data. I am verifying that the mock data structure is correctly utilized and that access control is appropriately enforced based on the decoded JWT.\n\n\n**Evaluating Authorization Details**\n\nI've just refined the authorization logic within the API route, paying close attention to various authorization response codes. Specifically, I'm confirming error handling for unauthorized users and inactive accounts, returning appropriate status codes and error messages using `NextResponse.json`. I'm meticulously checking the logic for `401` and `403` status codes, and the correct retrieval and return of the caller object.\n\n\n**Validating Response Data**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the data returned from my authorization process. I'm verifying the accurate filtering of project, operation, document, invoice, support ticket, and governance data based on the caller's client ID. I'm also confirming correct counts for active projects, operations, and verified documents for the authorized user, to be returned properly from the API.\n\n\n**Calculating Dashboard Statistics**\n\nI'm now calculating all the dashboard counts. I've successfully implemented calculations for verified documents, unpaid invoices, open support tickets, and flagged governance items. I'm also sorting and slicing data to retrieve the most recent projects, operations, documents, and invoices, confirming the backend now returns everything as expected for the UI.\n\n\n**Finalizing Summary Output**\n\nI'm now completing the final summary object to be returned by the API. I've finished integrating all the data, including recent projects, operations, documents, invoices, support tickets, and governance items. I'm verifying all fields for accurate representation and confirm the data structure is well-formed.\n\n\n**Confirming Admin Implementation**\n\nI'm now cross-referencing the client and admin routes to ensure consistency and correctness. I've verified that the admin route accurately leverages the mock data for user and project data, mirroring the client side. I'm focusing on ensuring data structures are identical and that the appropriate counts and records are retrieved and presented accurately.\n\n\n"}}
