{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:23:36.781Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"waqccaun","input":{"summary":"Built and verified the MVP Dashboard Summary APIs for both administrative and client-specific dashboards. \n\nKey Implementations & Resolutions:\n1. **Admin Dashboard Summary API (`/api/v1/dashboard/admin`)**: Designed and implemented the API to return global aggregates and arrays of the most recent 5 records across clients for active projects, client accounts, AI operations, documents, billing invoices, support tickets, and active governance alerts.\n2. **Client Dashboard Summary API (`/api/v1/dashboard/client`)**: Designed and implemented the API to return tenant-isolated statistics, counts, and recent records tailored to the specific `client_id` of the authorized user. It covers projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, open support tickets, and active governance checks.\n3. **Role-Based Access Control & Tenant Separation**: Implemented verification of Bearer JWT tokens via local security modules. Prevented cross-tenant access for client roles (returning 403 Forbidden on invalid query params) while allowing GFF administrators to explicitly filter by client ID.\n4. **Data Sourcing from Persistent Store**: Integrated API data sourcing dynamically from the memory-persisted global models in `lib/api-auth.ts`, ensuring live updates/persistence without hardcoded mock layouts.\n5. **Robust Test Validation**: Verified all endpoints and access rules successfully by compiling and executing the automated test suite `scripts/test-dashboard-apis.js` (which passed fully). Cleaned up temporary compilation directories.\n6. **Code Quality & Build Safety**: Verified compilation and eslint constraints using type checking (`npx tsc --noEmit`) and listing rules (`npm run lint`), passing with 0 errors. All guardrails (no catch-all slug routes, no PublicRoutePage, no external database or auth requirements, no modification to the landing page) have been strictly honored.","verified":true}}}
